text.tspan: Equality of civil liberties across social groups, World
Based on the expert assessments and index by V-Dem, weighted by countries' populations. It captures
the extent to which social groups — defined by language, ethnicity, religion, race, region, and/or caste —
are free from forced labor, have property rights and access to the justice system, and enjoy freedoms of
movement. Higher scores mean more equality.
Data source: OWID based on V-Dem (v13); Gapminder (v6); HYDE (v3.2); UN (2022)
